First time trying. Came in for an iced coffee, ended up getting a whole spread. Had the chicken masala sandwich and the pork momos (dumplings) for lunch on 07/16/20. So much deliciousness!! 100 percent coming back.
The best chai latte I’ve ever had, I got from here! I’ll definitely be back!

Since I had the day off, we decided to stop down to Himalayan Java for a lunchtime snack. Sag, the owner, is the man and I really liked the place. The spot had a neighborhood feel and that shined through as Sag greeted so many of the customers with handshakes and/or hugs.  The hot chocolate and coffees were all good as well as the cinnamon coffee cake that we ordered. We even got to try some Mo Mo which was pretty excellent. The sauce used has a very unique flavor that tastes like ginger and some kind of curry. There is probably more to it than that I'm sure.  The service was wonderful and the cashier even remembered my name. That coupled with the way the owner interacts with the customers would bring me back. I'm a huge fan establishments effete the owner mashes a point to be out on the floor.
Nice place to stop in for a coffee and a pastry. Cozy atmosphere and welcoming staff, I could spend hours in here hanging out, sipping coffee and reading a good book

So good! Everything I have ordered so far has been so delicious and the staff is great! They always help me find a drink that I would like because I am not a huge coffee drinker and everything I have tried so far has been delicious. Top recommendations are honey latte and the honey hot lemon tea.

This is my favorite coffee shop in the old market area. The outdoor seating is nice and the indoor is comfortable as well. They seem to allow dogs in which is cool.  Coffee selection is massive. Coffee strength and flavor is amazing! The eats they have are good. Prices are well.  I'd come here over Starbucks any day of the week!  The Browniecinno is amazing! Or just straight iced coffee is good too.
The Himalayan Chai is great, the paninis are tasty and the chicken momos are the highlight of my Wednesday.
The honey lemon green tea is exactly what my sore throat needed, and it's always a chill come in this place.

This is the best coffee shop in town, the people are lovely and great be around.  They roast their coffee in house, and if you know anything about coffee, you know just how important that is.  Highly recommend!

Come for the momos (Tibetan dumplings) on Wednesdays and Saturdays (11:30-1:30)! They’re delicious! The spices are perfect and getting the blend of the spicy sauces gives you a kick but doesn’t leave you sweating. I also recommend the Himalayan chai. The coffee is also quite strong and delicious.

The coffee and food was great! Everything tasted wonderful. The cashier who helped me was so sweet and provided such great service. The other employees were also very friendly. I will definitely be going back!

Cinnamon pound cake... nom nom nom. I would  COME BACK to Omaha for this! I would have this shipped to me before I ordered Omaha Steaks online! Perfect fusion of sugar, almond, cinnamon and vanilla— it’s PERFECT. GREAT with coffee or solo!!

One darn sexy cup of café. Friendly does not begin to describe the people who work here. They go above and beyond to learn your name and remember it along with your favorite drink order. it is definitely a coffee shop you can effectively work from if you still use paper and need to have something printed. There is space to sit outside and enjoy the weather and plenty of sitting inside as well. Take a minute or two to look over the menu. Their food offerings are definitely ethnic and definitely worth trying.
Delightful people and amazing coffee! Wide variety of latte options and teas. Very very good lunch options as well.
Every visit to Himalayan Java is a great one. Staff is so friendly, food is amazing, coffee is the best in Omaha. And don't even get me started on how great the momo is!

teas are awsome! and the momos are a specialty

This place was the best part of my Omaha trip. The vibe is super chill and cozy. The staff were super friendly and made me feel very welcomed. I happened to be in town on a Wednesday so, of course, I had to try the momos for the first time. They were absolutely delicious. The filling was very well seasoned and the size were huge so I was stuffed after 8 of them. The best part though was the spicy sauce. I would have been glad to just buy the sauce in a bottle to put on everything. I also had a smoothie and some Himalayan soup. All good, all worth the treck in the snow. Wish we had one in Atlanta.
Genuine staff, amazing service, and such good food!! 🥰  I go there often and have never had a bad experience.

Downtown Omaha is strange.  It’s a ghost town.  One of the only cities I’ve been to that doesn’t really have a shopping district, the streets are barren of traffic and cars, there’s hardly even any foot traffic...  So, I was surprised to find good coffee since I started thinking no one even lives or works down here.  This hot cup of yummy latte is exactly what I needed in this frigid day....  Thanks Himalayan!
This place is seriously awesome

Was in Omaha to visit my niece and we tried this coffee shop.  The coffee was excellent and the cinnamon bread was delicious.  The two young ladies were so friendly and welcoming.  We were able to bring the dog inside also.  A great place to have a coffee and visit with family and friends.  Very comfortable.

HJ checked off all my boxes. I enjoyed a Carmel marshmallow steamer and a Carmel bread pudding muffin. I was treated VERY well and looking to go again tomorrow before leaving Omaha.

I have been here a couple times now. The place has a great staff & wide selection of coffees & snacks. The shop itself is quite large and has ample seating. Lots of board games, tables & space for books, laptops etc. On any trip in you can observe numerous college kids sipping coffee & doing homework etc. I personally enjoyed the view out front and the people watching from it. Downtown Omaha has no shortage of interesting personalities on display. I would definitely recommend this coffee shop if you're in the area. My only complaint would be the back in, parking out front. It's caused me to skip this place and go to another nearby coffee shop on more then one occasion.

Went for my first time a few days ago, oh lord.. I love this place. The customer service was amazing! They explained to me the drinks answered all my questions with a friendly attitude. I went and worked on my journal and it was a cute cafe to get inspired and to work. I will definitely be going back!!

I am from Clarksville, Tennessee and just arrived to Omaha last night. I really wanted to visit a nice little coffee shop to sit and read before exploring the city. I ordered a medium iced coffee with vanilla, and a grilled chicken panini with provolone and whole wheat bread. Within 5 minutes they delivered my food to the table I was reading at. The coffee was unlike any coffee I've had before - it was AMAZING! The panini was very warm and the cheese was melted perfectly throughout the sandwich (not just in the middle) and they were very generous with the chicken. I enjoyed my visit there and will definitely come back before I leave and recommend everyone who comes to Omaha to give it a visit.

I'm so glad I found this place!  We were trying to find a quick bite and drink before a show at the Orpheum, and it was perfect.  Plenty of drink options, from cold to hot, smoothies, milk substitutes, sugar free, etc.  I don't usually get cold drinks, and definitely not smoothies, but this day was a particularly hot one, so I ordered a strawberry smoothie, and it was SO refreshing!  Standard coffee house snacks like bagels, muffins and shortbreads. They also have paninis for lunch, and some of the best dumplings I've EVER had!  Dining area is small and cozy, but comfortable. They have games to play it you're just hanging out with some friends.  The staff was friendly and warm.  We're definitely going to be repeat customers!

Love this fantastic little cafe in downtown Omaha!  We were in town for a wedding, staying right around the corner at the Residence Inn, when I found this little gem. I don't mind walking a couple blocks through blustering cold winds for a good cup off coffee and a quaint place to hang out for a bit—Himalayan Java is the perfect spot. The building is very unassuming but the interior transports you out of Nebraska with it's huge Everest poster, welcoming couches, and colorful flags swooping from the ceiling. The coffee is delicious, I stuck with my usual latte while my MIL quite enjoyed an Americana. We were very temped by the large assortment of lovely pastries, trying a raspberry scone—it was really good—and had plans to go back for lunch to try the "momos", which another customer raved about, but alas were caught up in wedding festivities. Next time!  I highly recommend taking a break for coffee and treats in this inviting cafe.
Tomato soup may be my favorite tomato soup that I've ever had.
